<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{interior mozart's apartment living room night 1780's}
<A>__{explosive laughter as mozart and schikaneder enter the apartment, very pleased with themselves and accompanied by the three actresses. the front door opens, very gingerly. mozart, still rather drunk, sticks his head into the room, anxious not to make a noise. he sees the strangers and breaks into a smile.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{oh. everybody's here! we've got guests. good. i've brought some more.}
<A>__{he opens the door wide to admit schikaneder and the girls.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{we'll have a little party. come in. come in. you know herr schikaneder?}
<P>__{(to a girl)}
<D>__{this is! a very nice girl.}
<C>__{constanze}
<P>__{(standing up)}
<D>__{wolfi.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{yes, my love?}
<C>__{constanze}
<D>__{these gentlemen are from salzburg.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{salzburg. we were just talking about salzburg.}
<P>__{(to the two men, jubilantly)}
<D>__{if you've come from my friend the fartsbishop, you've arrived at just the right moment. because i've got good news for him. i'm done with vienna. it's over, finished, done with! done with! done with!}
<C>__{constanze}
<D>__{wolfi! your father is dead.}
<C>__{mozart}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{constanze}
<D>__{your father is dead.}
<A>__{the first loud chord of the statue scene from don giovanni sounds. mozart stares.}
